Here's the recommended structure:

**1. Abstract the HTTP dependency**

```csharp
// In your MCP server project
public interface IApiClient
{
    Task<OrderResult> GetOrderAsync(string id);
}

public class RealApiClient(HttpClient http) : IApiClient
{
    public async Task<OrderResult> GetOrderAsync(string id)
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<OrderResult>($"/orders/{id}");
}
```

**2. Inject it into your tool class**

```csharp
[McpServerToolType]
public class OrderTools(IApiClient api)
{
    [McpServerTool, Description("Get order by ID")]
    public async Task<string> GetOrder(string orderId)
    {
        var order = await api.GetOrderAsync(orderId);
        return $"Order {order.Id}: {order.Status}";
    }
}
```

**3. Create the test project**

```
MyMcpServer/
├── src/
│   └── MyMcpServer/
│       ├── IApiClient.cs
│       ├── RealApiClient.cs
│       └── OrderTools.cs
└── tests/
    └── MyMcpServer.Tests/
        ├── MyMcpServer.Tests.csproj
        └── OrderToolsTests.cs
```

```xml
<!-- MyMcpServer.Tests.csproj -->
<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk" Version="17.*" />
    <PackageReference Include="xunit" Version="2.*" />
    <PackageReference Include="xunit.runner.visualstudio" Version="2.*" />
    <PackageReference Include="NSubstitute" Version="5.*" />
    <ProjectReference Include="../../src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>
</Project>
```

**4. Write tests with a mock**

```csharp
using NSubstitute;
using Xunit;

public class OrderToolsTests
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task GetOrder_ReturnsFormattedString()
    {
        // Arrange
        var api = Substitute.For<IApiClient>();
        api.GetOrderAsync("42").Returns(new OrderResult { Id = "42", Status = "Shipped" });
        var tools = new OrderTools(api);

        // Act
        var result = await tools.GetOrder("42");

        // Assert
        Assert.Equal("Order 42: Shipped", result);
    }
}
```

**Key principles:**

- **Interface extraction** — wrap the HTTP calls behind `IApiClient` so tests never touch the network.
- **Constructor injection** — pass the dependency in; your DI container wires the real one, tests wire a mock.
- **Mock library** (NSubstitute, Moq, etc.) — stubs return values and verifies calls without a real server.
- **Alternative:** If you'd rather test closer to the wire, inject a fake `HttpMessageHandler` into `HttpClient` instead of abstracting with an interface. This tests your serialization too, but couples tests to HTTP details.
